This step is only required if your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment does not already have the stemcell version <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> requires. For more information about importing stemcells, see [Importing and Managing Stemcells](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/<%= product_info['local_product_version'].to_s.sub('.','-') %>/opsguide/managing-stemcells.html).

To download the stemcell version <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> requires:

1. Go to the [Stemcell product page](https://network.pivotal.io/products/stemcells) on VMware Tanzu Network. You may have to log in.

1. Download the appropriate stemcell version targeted for your IaaS.

1. In the <%= vars.ops_manager %> Installation Dashboard, navigate to **Stemcell Library**.

1. Click **Import Stemcell** to import the downloaded stemcell `.tgz` file.

1. When prompted, enable the <%= vars.ops_manager %> product checkbox to stage your stemcell.

1. Click **Apply Stemcell to Products**.
